3. CPU :- 
-This is my Project which is not making in Group and It's Simple Funda is the How to the CPU Gets data than fetch it and how it goes in working part this concept is the Heart Of the CPU.
-Data Flow :-
Memory → Instruction Register  
Instruction Register → Control Unit  
Register A + Register B → ALU  
ALU → Accumulator  
Accumulator → Output
-CPU Used Components :-
| CPU Block                | Component Used                     | Purpose                                |
| ------------------------ | ---------------------------------- | -------------------------------------- |
| **Clock Unit**           | NE555 Timer IC                     | Generates clock pulses                 |
| **Register A**           | 74LS173                            | Stores Operand A                       |
| **Register B**           | 74LS173                            | Stores Operand B                       |
| **ALU**                  | 74LS181                            | Performs Arithmetic & Logic operations |
| **Accumulator**          | 74LS173                            | Stores ALU result                      |
| **Program Counter**      | 74LS161                            | Generates next instruction address     |
| **Instruction Register** | 74LS173                            | Holds current instruction              |
| **Memory**               | 28C16 EEPROM                       | Stores program                         |
| **Control Unit**         | 74LS138 Decoder                    | Generates control signals              |
| **Output Display**       | 7-Segment Display (Common Cathode) | Displays output                        |
| **Data Bus Buffer**      | 74LS245                            | Controls data flow direction           |

Accumlator Connections (Heart Of CPU):-
| Pin Group | Connected To       |
| --------- | ------------------ |
| A0–A3     | Register A Outputs |
| B0–B3     | Register B Outputs |
| S0–S3     | Control Unit       |
| M (Mode)  | Control Unit       |
| Carry In  | Control Unit       |
| F0–F3     | Accumulator Inputs |

